Description: After the end of 17-21 WRC+ era, Rally1 regulation is a new start for top level WRC. In order to create a competitive car, a pre-season prototype variant is built for testing. This prototype is using existing monocoque chassis, suspension and engine for cost reduction. Wheelbase has been increased to about 2600mm, tarmac dampers have a bit more extension travel. The 2025 spec is set without hybrid unit and a 35mm restrictor.
